{
  "audit_target": "godotengine/godot 4.3-stable",
  "audit_scope": "GDScript VM security boundaries",
  "files": [
    {
      "category": "GDScript VM — Bytecode Interpreter / Opcode Dispatch",
      "files": [
        {
          "path": "modules/gdscript/gdscript_vm.cpp",
          "description": "The sole implementation file for the GDScript bytecode interpreter. Contains GDScriptFunction::call(), the main dispatch loop that executes every opcode. Uses a computed-goto / jump-table (OPCODES_TABLE macro) for dispatch. Enforces a thread-local call-depth counter (MAX_CALL_DEPTH = 2048) to prevent stack overflow. Handles stack frame allocation (alloca_size), argument validation, and resume from await (CallState). Also contains debug helpers _profile_count_as_native, _get_var_type, _get_element_type.",
          "key_functions": [
            "GDScriptFunction::call(GDScriptInstance*, const Variant**, int, Callable::CallError&, CallState*)"
          ],
          "security_notes": [
            "Stack-overflow guard: thread_local call_depth checked against MAX_CALL_DEPTH=2048 before every call.",
            "Argument count validation (CALL_ERROR_TOO_MANY_ARGUMENTS / CALL_ERROR_TOO_FEW_ARGUMENTS) before stack allocation.",
            "Null/freed-object checks emitted as METHOD_CALL_ON_NULL_VALUE_ERROR / METHOD_CALL_ON_FREED_INSTANCE_ERROR macros.",
            "All type-safety checks (OPCODE_TYPE_TEST_*, OPCODE_ASSIGN_TYPED_*, OPCODE_CAST_TO_*) are performed inside this loop."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "category": "GDScript VM — Call Frame Management & Opcode Definitions",
      "files": [
        {
          "path": "modules/gdscript/gdscript_function.h",
          "description": "Declares GDScriptFunction (the compiled representation of one GDScript function) and GDScriptFunctionState (coroutine/await state). Key inner types: Opcode enum (all ~150 opcodes), Address enum (24-bit address space with ADDR_TYPE_STACK/CONSTANT/MEMBER), FixedAddresses (ADDR_STACK_SELF=0, ADDR_STACK_CLASS=1, ADDR_STACK_NIL=2), CallState struct (serialised frame for await resume), StackDebug struct. Private fields include _code_ptr, _stack_size, _instruction_args_size, _argument_count, _default_arg_count, and typed dispatch-table pointer arrays (operator_funcs, setters, getters, methods, lambdas, etc.).",
          "key_classes": [
            "GDScriptDataType",
            "GDScriptFunction",
            "GDScriptFunction::Opcode (enum)",
            "GDScriptFunction::Address (enum)",
            "GDScriptFunction::FixedAddresses (enum)",
            "GDScriptFunction::CallState (struct)",
            "GDScriptFunction::StackDebug (struct)",
            "GDScriptFunctionState"
          ],
          "security_notes": [
            "MAX_CALL_DEPTH = 2048 defined here as a constexpr.",
            "Address space is 24-bit (ADDR_BITS=24, ADDR_MASK=0xFFFFFF); upper bits encode address type — bounds are not checked at the C++ level beyond array-size assertions in debug builds.",
            "GDScriptDataType::is_type() performs runtime type checks for NATIVE kind via ClassDB::is_parent_class(), for SCRIPT/GDSCRIPT kind via pointer equality — this is the type-safety enforcement point.",
            "CallState captures the full frame (stack bytes, ip, line, defarg) for coroutine resume — no sandboxing between resumed frames."
          ]
        },
        {
          "path": "modules/gdscript/gdscript_function.cpp",
          "description": "Implements GDScriptFunction constructor/destructor, get_constant(), get_global_name(), debug_get_stack_member_state(), and _get_default_variant_for_data_type(). Also implements GDScriptFunctionState (coroutine state machine, _signal_callback, resume).",
          "key_functions": [
            "GDScriptFunction::GDScriptFunction()",
            "GDScriptFunction::~GDScriptFunction()",
            "GDScriptFunction::debug_get_stack_member_state(int, List<Pair<StringName,int>>*)",
            "GDScriptFunctionState::resume(Variant)"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "category": "GDScript VM — Script & Instance (tool/non-tool gate, callp)",
      "files": [
        {
          "path": "modules/gdscript/gdscript.h",
          "description": "Declares GDScript (the Script resource), GDScriptInstance (ScriptInstance implementation), GDScriptNativeClass, and GDScriptLanguage. GDScript holds member_functions (HashMap<StringName, GDScriptFunction*>), the tool flag, and the valid flag. GDScriptLanguage is the singleton language backend.",
          "key_classes": [
            "GDScript",
            "GDScriptInstance",
            "GDScriptNativeClass",
            "GDScriptLanguage"
          ]
        },
        {
          "path": "modules/gdscript/gdscript.cpp",
          "description": "Implements GDScript::reload() (parse → analyze → compile pipeline), GDScriptInstance::callp() (method dispatch into GDScriptFunction::call()), and GDScript::can_instantiate() (tool/scripting-enabled gate). Contains the critical tool-mode permission checks.",
          "key_functions": [
            "GDScript::reload(bool p_keep_state)",
            "GDScript::can_instantiate() const",
            "GDScriptInstance::callp(const StringName&, const Variant**, int, Callable::CallError&)"
          ],
          "security_notes": [
            "GDScript::can_instantiate() (line ~249): returns valid && (tool || ScriptServer::is_scripting_enabled()) under TOOLS_ENABLED — non-tool scripts cannot be instantiated in the editor.",
            "GDScript::reload() (line ~793): bool can_run = ScriptServer::is_scripting_enabled() || is_tool() — controls whether static initialisation runs at reload time.",
            "GDScriptInstance::callp() (line 2022): walks the script inheritance chain (sptr = sptr->_base) looking up member_functions; calls GDScriptFunction::call() directly — no additional permission check at call time beyond what the VM enforces.",
            "GDScriptInstance::callp() special-cases _ready to call _call_implicit_ready_recursively first."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
